s.com/?p=293',0,'revision','',0),
(294,5,'2024-03-30 17:47:37','2024-03-30 17:47:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From his review of my Frontend page:  <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/your-front-end-development-journey-a-step-by-step-roadmap/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"299\">Your Front-End Development Journey: A Step-by-Step Roadmap</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":353,\"width\":\"690px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/work-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\" style=\"width:690px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hi! My name is Philemon Bahati, I am a Frontend Web Developer with 5+ years of experience in developing websites. I have a passion for creating user-friendly, visually appealing, and functional websites. My expertise lies in HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, React js, Tailwind, and Bootstrap. I have a strong understanding of web standards and accessibility guidelines.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Philemon\'s contributions','','publish','closed','closed','','philemons-contributions','','','2024-04-26 09:11:25','2024-04-26 09:11:25','',295,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=294',0,'page','',0),
(295,1,'2024-03-30 17:33:29','2024-03-30 17:33:29','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are the contributors to this site.  I am very grateful to their contributions:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/contributors/philemons-contributions/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"294\">Bahati Philemon</a> is one of my first readers. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/ashuza-destins-contributions/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"317\">ASHUZA Destin</a> is one of my first readers. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Contributors','','publish','closed','closed','','contributors','','','2024-04-16 21:54:46','2024-04-16 21:54:46','',22,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=295',0,'page','',0),
(296,1,'2024-03-30 17:33:29','2024-03-30 17:33:29','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are the contributors to this site.  I am very grateful to their contributions:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bahati Philemon is one of my first readers. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Contributors','','inherit','closed','closed','','295-revision-v1','','','2024-03-30 17:33:29','2024-03-30 17:33:29','',295,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=296',0,'revision','',0),
(298,1,'2024-03-30 17:35:37','2024-03-30 17:35:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Michael lives near Cedar Park, Texas with his wife Mary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":\"nowrap\",\"justifyContent\":\"space-between\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":39,\"width\":\"309px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"aspectRatio\":\"1.3360655737704918\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IMG_1613-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-39\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.3360655737704918;width:309px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":169,\"width\":\"324px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\" style=\"width:324px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Michael is a 40 year veteran software engineer.  The last 33 years was as a principal systems developer at <a href=\"http://www.sas.com\">SAS Institute</a>.  His main responsibility was the <a href=\"https://www.sas.com/en_us/search.html?q=metadata%20server\">enterprise metadata server</a> that connects all SAS products. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He is now happily retired, but not yet done with the field.  This site is home base for his new focus of mentoring programmers in the art of software engineering.   The main emphasis is individuals living in a places that do not have software development jobs.  This means that their best opportunity is to go freelance.   Doing so allows them to stay in their culture and home community.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While freelancing is a start, there are also opportunities to do so much more as part of a larger development team focused on many open source software projects.   This is something that I am moving into myself.  Join me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Acknowledgement of Contributors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am grateful to those who have read this site and made valuable contributions through feedback and contributed material.     <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/contributors/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"295\">See this full list.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:social-links -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links\"><!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\",\"service\":\"github\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/michaelkentburns/?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Ad_flagship3_feed%3B6Dj3E8auRSy51Ad%2BgA7N%2FQ%3D%3D\",\"service\":\"linkedin\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\",\"service\":\"mail\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://www.facebook.com/michael.burns.906\",\"service\":\"facebook\"} /--></ul>\n<!-- /wp:social-links -->\n\n<!-- wp:social-links -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:social-links -->','About Michael','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2024-03-30 17:35:37','2024-03-30 17:35:37','',22,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=298',0,'revision','',0),
(299,5,'2024-03-30 17:42:42','2024-03-30 17:42:42','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Note:  This is also available as a <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Philemons-Front-End-Development-road-map.pdf\">downloadable PDF</a> for your use.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The world of web development is vast and exciting, and front-end development is at the forefront of creating user experiences that are both beautiful and functional. If you\'re looking to embark on a career as a front-end developer, this roadmap will guide you through the essential skills and technologies you need to master.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Phase 1: Building the Foundation</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Big Three:</strong> This journey starts with the fundamentals – HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>HTML:</strong>&nbsp;The building blocks of web pages, HTML structures content and defines the overall layout.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>CSS:</strong>&nbsp;Responsible for styling and visual presentation, CSS brings your web pages to life with colors, fonts, and layouts.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>JavaScript:</strong>&nbsp;The language that adds interactivity to web pages, allowing for animations, user input handling, and dynamic content.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Master the Basics:</strong>&nbsp;Focus on getting comfortable with the core functionalities of each language. Practice writing clean and well-structured code.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Phase 2: Deepening Your Skillset</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Going Beyond the Basics:</strong> Once you have a solid foundation, delve deeper into advanced concepts in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>HTML:</strong>&nbsp;Learn about semantic HTML, forms, and web components.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>CSS:</strong>&nbsp;Explore advanced CSS topics like preprocessors (SASS, LESS), responsive design for different screen sizes, and CSS frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind CSS).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>JavaScript:</strong>&nbsp;Master object-oriented programming concepts, understand the Document Object Model (DOM), and explore asynchronous programming with promises or async/await.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Version Control with Git:</strong>&nbsp;Learn Git, a version control system, to manage your code effectively and collaborate with others on projects.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Phase 3: Expanding Your Horizons</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Frontend Frameworks:</strong> Dive into popular front-end frameworks that streamline development and provide pre-built components. Popular choices include React, Angular, and Vue.js.<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Benefits:</strong>&nbsp;Frameworks offer faster development, reusable components, and a structured approach to building complex web applications.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>JavaScript Libraries:</strong>&nbsp;Explore powerful JavaScript libraries that enhance your development capabilities. Examples include jQuery (DOM manipulation), Axios (making HTTP requests), and Lodash (utility functions).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Build Projects:</strong>&nbsp;The best way to solidify your learning is by building projects. Start with small, personal projects and gradually progress to larger, more complex applications. This hands-on experience is invaluable for your portfolio.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Phase 4: Continuous Learning and Growth</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Stay Updated:</strong>&nbsp;The web development landscape is constantly evolving. Keep yourself updated with the latest trends and technologies by following industry blogs, attending conferences, and participating in online communities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong>&nbsp;While technical skills are crucial, don\'t neglect soft skills like communication, collaboration, and problem-solving. These will be essential when working in a team environment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Network and Build Your Portfolio:</strong>&nbsp;Connect with other developers, build a strong online presence, and showcase your work on a portfolio website.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Your Front-End Development Journey: A Step-by-Step Roadmap','','publish','open','closed','','your-front-end-development-journey-a-step-by-step-roadmap','','','2024-04-01 20:15:29','2024-04-01 20:15:29','',294,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=299',0,'page','',0),
